Okay, that sqlalchemy.exc.InvalidRequestError: Mapper 'Mapper[User(users)]' has no property 'prompts' error is very specific. It means that when SQLAlchemy is setting up the relationships between your models, the Prompt model's owner relationship is trying to link to a prompts attribute on the User model (via back_populates="prompts"), but it cannot find such an attribute on the User model.

This usually happens if:

The prompts relationship was not added to your app/models/user.py file.
There's a typo in the back_populates string in either app/models/prompt.py or app/models/user.py.
A circular import issue is preventing SQLAlchemy from fully processing one of the models before trying to link them (though TYPE_CHECKING usually helps with this).
Let's ensure your /story_app/app/models/user.py file has the correct prompts relationship defined. I'll provide the full content for this file, incorporating the relationships for created_stories, uploaded_documents, and the new prompts.

